## Prioritized Remediation Plan

| Priority | Fix | Effort | Impact |
|----------|-----|--------|--------|
| 1 | Remove `if/else` — split into two targeted tests | Low | Eliminates hidden untested path |
| 2 | Add assertions to `CompletesWithoutError` | Low | Eliminates false-pass risk |
| 3 | Replace `try/catch` with `Assert.ThrowsException` | Low | Cleaner, safer exception testing |
| 4 | Replace `Thread.Sleep` with `async/await` | Medium | Eliminates flakiness + speeds up suite |
| 5 | Inline or embed the CSV test data | Medium | Fixes portability — test will actually run in CI |
| 6 | Break up the eager workflow test | Medium | Improves failure diagnostics |
| 7 | Name the magic numbers | Low | Improves readability |
| 8 | Replace `ToString()` assertion | Low | Reduces brittleness |
| 9 | Remove unused `_logger` from fixture | Low | Reduces noise |

The one clean test — `ValidateOrder_NullOrder_ThrowsArgumentNullException` — is a good example to follow: focused scope, proper framework API usage, and a clear assertion on a specific property.
